  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>At 8th level, you can emit a 30-foot aura to either ward off or welcome emotional influence for a number of rounds per day equal to your wizard level. If you choose to ward, you and your allies within this aura receive a +4&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/glossary#TOC-Morale-Bonus\">morale bonus</a>&nbsp;on saves against mind-affecting spells and effects, and any fear effects targeting you or your allies are reduced by one step (<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/conditions#TOC-Shaken\">shaken</a>&nbsp;has no effect,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/conditions#TOC-Frightened\">frightened</a>&nbsp;becomes&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/conditions#TOC-Shaken\">shaken</a>, and&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/conditions#TOC-Panicked\">panicked</a>&nbsp;becomes&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/conditions#TOC-Frightened\">frightened</a>). If you chose to enhance emotional influence, enemies within the aura receive a â€“2 penalty on saves against mind-affecting spells and effects. These rounds do not need to be consecutive.</p>",
